                     /synonym="modified haloalkane dehalogenase"
                     /note="HaloTag7 self-labeling protein tag, 297 aa.
                     Engineered monomeric haloalkane dehalogenase derived from
                     Rhodococcus rhodochrous DhaA, carrying mutations that (i)
                     abolish the second hydrolytic step so the enzyme-substrate
                     covalent intermediate is trapped, and (ii) improve folding,
                     solubility, and binding kinetics. Forms a rapid,
                     essentially irreversible covalent ester bond with synthetic
                     chloroalkane ligands. No coordinate-verified internal
                     sub-features were retained; the catalytic residues
                     (nucleophilic Asp at the alpha/beta-hydrolase nucleophile
                     elbow, motif IGMGKSDK; the engineered His->Phe that
                     prevents hydrolytic release) are mechanistic and are
                     captured as functional_claims rather than as residue-level
                     features."
